observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor issue a directive to the Inventory Committee to perform the following tasks, and monitor their compliance thereof:
5. conduct a comprehensive physical count of all RPCPPE;
6. prepare a RPCPPE;
7. Submit to the COA Audit Team Leader (ATL) and Supervising Auditor (SA) a request for authority to derecognize non-existing/missing PPEs for which accountability could no longer be pinpointed, together with the required supporting documents, particularly the certified copy of the report of investigation.
We also recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
8. Prepare adjusting entries to reclassify from the PPE accounts the identifies items with unit cost below the ₱50,000.00 threshold totaling ₱1,355,916.00 to the appropriate expense account supported with Inventory Custodian Slips;
9. Adopt the procedures prescribed for the cleansing and one-time validation of its PPE records after the conduct of investigation on missing/unaccounted properties;
10. Initiate the turn-over of the completed projects costing ₱1,250,059.57 to the respective recipient Barangays, supported with Deed of Donation and Property Transfer Reports (PTRs), and effect adjustments in the books; and
11. Maintain and update PPE Ledger Cards for each category of assets.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant:
12. Verify the discrepancies transferred between the Notes to Financial Statements, the GL Balance of the Trust Liability-DRRM account and the Utilization Report, and make the necessary corrections;
13. Maintain subsidiary ledgers for the Trust Liability-DRRM account pertaining to transfers of unexpended LDRRMF by year that the transfer is made;
14. Tally the amounts and balances of LDRRM Fund presented in the Notes to Financial Statements and ensure that it is consistent with the source documents/registries.

1. Identify the valid claimants in the current Accounts Payable and prepare the list comprising the balance, supported with the pertinent Disbursement Vouchers and documents,;
2. Revert to the Government Equity account those payables without valid claimants, including the ₱40,807.35 in the Special Education Fund which have remained in the books for more than two years; furnish the Municipal Budget Officer with a copy of the Journal Entry Voucher on the reversion; and maintain a record of the reverted A/Ps; and
3. Set an official deadline on the submission of claims at yearend and accept for processing only the claims which are supported with complete and necessary documents.
